      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in Business Day on Saturday about a report from the board of the computer company CA contending that its founder, Charles B. Wang, masterminded an accounting fraud rendered a word incorrectly in Mr. Wang's response. In a statement, he called the report ''fallacious'' -- not ''fictitious.''</p>
